00:59:28,361 --> 00:59:31,638
Isn't it strange when you
can't even trust your own fingers?

795
00:59:31,970 --> 00:59:33,760
And don't ask me how I feel.

796
00:59:33,784 --> 00:59:35,418
I wouldn't think of it.

797
00:59:39,167 --> 00:59:40,467
Evan.

798
00:59:41,855 --> 00:59:43,155
Crock.

799
00:59:44,450 --> 00:59:46,200
Crock is… gun.

800
00:59:46,541 --> 00:59:49,467
No way I'll be able to bring
a gun with me tomorrow.

801
00:59:49,905 --> 00:59:52,845
Mbui frisked me today.
He'll frisk me again tomorrow.

802
00:59:53,708 --> 00:59:55,499
Well, how do you plan to do it?

803
00:59:55,523 --> 00:59:58,518
It's been so long,
thought about it so long,

804
00:59:59,371 --> 01:00:00,671
I'm not sure.

805
01:00:01,089 --> 01:00:03,478
Maybe I'll just let
the moment guide me.

806
01:00:03,864 --> 01:00:06,209
I've got a syringe and medication.

807
01:00:06,464 --> 01:00:07,763
One's quick and painless,

808
01:00:07,787 --> 01:00:09,584
the other's a
strychnine derivative…

809
01:00:09,608 --> 01:00:12,649
excruciating, takes over an hour.

810
01:00:13,177 --> 01:00:15,185
Or maybe I'll just get up close to him,

811
01:00:15,209 --> 01:00:18,449
slice him and let his blood
wash all over me.

812
01:00:19,858 --> 01:00:23,057
I don't feel comfortable
letting you go in there alone.

813
01:00:23,081 --> 01:00:24,571
I'll be all right.

814
01:00:25,923 --> 01:00:27,379
I brought a belt blade.

815
01:00:27,403 --> 01:00:30,445
I'll be able to get that through,
but that's about it.

816
01:00:33,325 --> 01:00:35,325
- So that's that then?
- Yeah.

817
01:00:36,376 --> 01:00:37,676
Milt…

818
01:00:38,411 --> 01:00:40,246
thanks for coming along.

819
01:00:40,876 --> 01:00:42,867
No problem, old sport.

820
01:01:13,921 --> 01:01:15,713
If I'm not out in an hour,

821
01:01:15,737 --> 01:01:17,603
do whatever you want.

822
01:01:39,440 --> 01:01:40,740
Please.

823
01:01:43,854 --> 01:01:45,426
Did you sleep well?

824
01:01:46,263 --> 01:01:48,470
Sometimes the heat is a problem.

825
01:02:20,425 --> 01:02:22,617
Open the briefcase.

826
01:04:02,229 --> 01:04:03,529
Dr. Cornel.

827
01:04:04,478 --> 01:04:05,667
Salaam alaikum.

828
01:04:05,691 --> 01:04:08,483
Salaam alaikum, Saeed Ali Hariri.

829
01:04:08,507 --> 01:04:11,629
Dr. Cornel, thank you.

830
01:04:12,024 --> 01:04:13,703
Thank you for coming.

831
01:04:13,727 --> 01:04:15,300
Forgive me for not…

832
01:04:16,174 --> 01:04:17,474
standing.

833
01:04:19,282 --> 01:04:21,285
Mbui, some tea.

834
01:04:23,558 --> 01:04:25,773
And those… those dates.

835
01:04:25,797 --> 01:04:27,097
Mind if I sit?

836
01:04:27,542 --> 01:04:28,842
Oh, please.

837
01:04:32,943 --> 01:04:36,429
Dr. Wangari has
provided me your records,

838
01:04:36,453 --> 01:04:38,132
your treatment history.

839
01:04:38,156 --> 01:04:41,930
Last night I was in contact
with several of my colleagues.

840
01:04:42,086 --> 01:04:43,386
Thank you.

841
01:04:45,854 --> 01:04:48,301
I noticed you were scheduled
three months ago

842
01:04:48,325 --> 01:04:49,991
for a bone marrow transplant,

843
01:04:50,015 --> 01:04:52,104
but I found no record of the procedure.

844
01:04:52,128 --> 01:04:54,193
Was there a problem with the donor?

845
01:04:54,217 --> 01:04:55,896
It was too dangerous.

846
01:04:55,920 --> 01:04:58,670
Uh, no sibling donor was possible,

847
01:04:58,694 --> 01:05:01,276
no compatible cousins.

848
01:05:01,300 --> 01:05:05,155
It is risky, but an unrelated donor

849
01:05:05,179 --> 01:05:10,192
can be found based on HLB
and DR histocompatibility.

850
01:05:13,796 --> 01:05:17,229
The university hospital
can assist in finding such a donor.

851
01:05:17,253 --> 01:05:18,977
We have a large database.

852
01:05:20,667 --> 01:05:22,280
Should have been done before.

853
01:05:22,304 --> 01:05:27,544
It is more dangerous now,
but we have no choice.

854
01:05:27,697 --> 01:05:32,877
At present, transplantation is
the only possible curative therapy.

855
01:05:33,477 --> 01:05:37,918
And… it can be done here?

856
01:05:37,942 --> 01:05:39,242
Yes.

857
01:05:43,778 --> 01:05:46,261
Excuse me,
I am not such a young man.

858
01:05:46,635 --> 01:05:48,290
Where is the toilet?

859
01:05:48,675 --> 01:05:50,522
Back and to the left.

860
01:05:51,516 --> 01:05:54,040
- So sorry.
- Oh, please. Please.

861
01:06:21,777 --> 01:06:24,515
There is a problem with the toilet.

862
01:06:24,733 --> 01:06:26,998
Mmm. Mbui.

863
01:06:33,107 --> 01:06:34,635
It won't flush.

864
01:06:35,300 --> 01:06:37,732
- You pulled the chain?
- I pulled the chain.

865
01:06:38,899 --> 01:06:42,532
There is something stuck… in there.

866
01:07:08,241 --> 01:07:09,896
I have to be honest.

867
01:07:11,036 --> 01:07:14,256
Your condition is
far worse than I imagined.

868
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:18,280
Your long-term chances
for survival are not good.

869
01:07:21,419 --> 01:07:24,169
Neither are your short-term chances.

870
01:07:29,052 --> 01:07:31,609
In fact, they are quite hopeless.

871
01:07:34,917 --> 01:07:37,004
It's because I'm not a doctor.

872
01:07:42,080 --> 01:07:45,726
My name isn't Iulian Cornel…

873
01:07:46,581 --> 01:07:49,192
and your name isn't Ali Hariri.

874
01:07:50,265 --> 01:07:51,565
Your name…

875
01:07:51,943 --> 01:07:53,750
is Muhammad Banir.

876
01:08:07,331 --> 01:08:08,784
Mr. Ruchowski.

877
01:08:11,042 --> 01:08:12,342
Evan Lake.

878
01:08:15,409 --> 01:08:17,539
- Where is your backup?
- Hmm?

879
01:08:18,044 --> 01:08:19,724
Your elite commandos.

880
01:08:20,528 --> 01:08:21,828
Oh.

881
01:08:22,206 --> 01:08:23,506
You came alone.

882
01:08:29,826 --> 01:08:31,672
How did you find me?

883
01:08:32,083 --> 01:08:36,956
Through the request for experimental
thalassemia medication, Decitabine.

884
01:08:37,927 --> 01:08:39,805
Family medical history.

885
01:08:42,275 --> 01:08:43,575
Yeah.

886
01:08:46,372 --> 01:08:47,672
So…

887
01:08:51,274 --> 01:08:52,574
how are you…

888
01:08:53,793 --> 01:08:55,653
How are you going to kill me?

889
01:08:57,528 --> 01:08:59,428
I- I-I don't know.

890
01:09:00,941 --> 01:09:02,941
How are you going to kill me?

891
01:09:03,312 --> 01:09:04,612
I don't know.

892
01:09:07,260 --> 01:09:09,191
What the hell are you doing?

893
01:09:10,848 --> 01:09:13,099
We have some time.

894
01:09:14,231 --> 01:09:15,813
Perhaps we can have that…

895
01:09:16,800 --> 01:09:21,481
conversation that I wanted to have
that time years ago.

896
01:09:21,717 --> 01:09:23,017
Huh?

897
01:09:24,203 --> 01:09:26,920
Perhaps you've read some of my writings?

898
01:09:27,895 --> 01:09:31,938
Mr. Lake, we strongly recommend you put
the matter of Muhammad Banir behind you.

899
01:09:31,962 --> 01:09:33,740
I didn't know you were still active.

900
01:09:35,967 --> 01:09:37,148
I contribute…

901
01:09:37,172 --> 01:09:40,280
a number of web sites
not under my name.

902
01:09:40,462 --> 01:09:44,004
Of course,
you are religious man, Mr. Lake?

903
01:09:44,036 --> 01:09:46,011
No, I'm not religious.

904
01:09:46,035 --> 01:09:47,796
I think you are.

905
01:09:47,820 --> 01:09:49,961
America, yeah?

906
01:09:49,985 --> 01:09:52,336
You see yourself as a religion…
America.

907
01:09:52,360 --> 01:09:55,305
I've written about this,
the American way of life.

908
01:09:55,979 --> 01:09:58,323
Have you been
to Greeley, Colorado?

909
01:09:58,839 --> 01:10:01,164
Sayyid Qutb…

910
01:10:01,188 --> 01:10:04,961
who went from Cairo
to Colorado State College in 1948.

911
01:10:04,985 --> 01:10:07,882
He said Greeley was
like paradise on earth.

912
01:10:09,365 --> 01:10:12,246
What Qutb saw was jahiliyyah, huh?

913
01:10:13,302 --> 01:10:16,182
Decadence,
promiscuity, pop music.

914
01:10:16,206 --> 01:10:17,974
"Baby, It's Cold Outside."

915
01:10:29,393 --> 01:10:33,175
The- the- the flirting
and the mixing of men and women,

916
01:10:33,199 --> 01:10:35,873
the disrespect… so no, he left.

917
01:10:35,946 --> 01:10:39,585
Went back to Egypt
and the movement was born.

918
01:10:39,609 --> 01:10:41,289
The Muslim Brotherhood.

919
01:10:41,379 --> 01:10:43,130
My father knew him.

920
01:10:43,324 --> 01:10:45,174
No, Nasser…

921
01:10:45,314 --> 01:10:47,349
Nasser executed him.

922
01:10:50,069 --> 01:10:51,796
It was too late.

923
01:10:52,649 --> 01:10:54,520
Fundamentalism,

924
01:10:55,062 --> 01:10:56,361
the message…

925
01:10:56,385 --> 01:10:58,017
from the prophet…

926
01:10:58,044 --> 01:11:00,118
was social justice!

927
01:11:00,142 --> 01:11:03,061
Better schools, better jobs.

928
01:11:03,085 --> 01:11:04,385
Mr. Lake.

929
01:11:05,391 --> 01:11:08,583
This doesn't just… just end.

930
01:11:09,104 --> 01:11:11,760
Are you still a believer?

931
01:11:12,386 --> 01:11:14,837
Hmm?
Do you still believe?

932
01:11:15,020 --> 01:11:16,922
I don't. I don't.

933
01:11:17,491 --> 01:11:21,446
My faith, it was…
it was taken from me.

934
01:11:22,012 --> 01:11:25,057
You think I'm playing games
with you, Mr. Lake?

935
01:11:25,081 --> 01:11:26,381
Huh?

936
01:11:27,298 --> 01:11:29,688
You think we are playing games?

937
01:11:29,712 --> 01:11:31,115
No, my name is Charles Ruchowski.

938
01:11:31,139 --> 01:11:32,759
While mullahs,
ayatollahs, they get rich.

939
01:11:32,790 --> 01:11:36,681
They have their orgies,
imprison their opponents.

940
01:11:36,705 --> 01:11:38,385
Why? Hmm? Why?

941
01:11:38,472 --> 01:11:41,024
I'm Charles Ruchowski.

942
01:11:41,048 --> 01:11:45,066
I'm a representative for Spirit Systems.

943
01:11:46,848 --> 01:11:50,811
The only hope
for Islam now is…

944
01:11:51,058 --> 01:11:52,873
Marx, hmm?

945
01:11:54,191 --> 01:11:55,865
Social justice.

946
01:11:56,589 --> 01:11:58,857
We like the fear.
<i>I</i> like the fear.

947
01:11:58,881 --> 01:12:00,288
I like the fear.

948
01:12:00,863 --> 01:12:03,294
Our believers, not so many.

949
01:12:03,780 --> 01:12:07,365
No, the truly dangerous people…

950
01:12:07,400 --> 01:12:09,394
are the ones who follow orders.

951
01:12:09,431 --> 01:12:11,243
Do you think it made any difference?

952
01:12:11,267 --> 01:12:12,757
What you did!

953
01:12:12,840 --> 01:12:16,429
You! You! You!

954
01:12:18,584 --> 01:12:19,884
Do you?

955
01:12:24,516 --> 01:12:31,603
Now, what is the name
of the source, Mr. Lake?

956
01:12:34,548 --> 01:12:36,856
You are sick too. Hmm?

957
01:12:36,880 --> 01:12:38,955
I see it, your face.

958
01:12:39,901 --> 01:12:42,698
You have a disease of the blood.

959
01:12:43,107 --> 01:12:45,419
My disease is in the brain.

960
01:12:45,576 --> 01:12:47,530
What sort of disease?

961
01:12:49,340 --> 01:12:51,279
I'm forgetting things.

962
01:12:51,701 --> 01:12:53,676
Ohh.

963
01:12:54,831 --> 01:12:56,555
There is a lot to forget.

964
01:14:45,437 --> 01:14:46,737
Evan.

965
01:14:46,858 --> 01:14:48,549
Come upstairs.

